    "Body": " Location: San Francisco or Remote At??Forte, we believe blockchain will enable new economic and creative opportunities for gamers around the world, and have assembled a world-class team of veterans from across the games industry\u2014and a $100M developer fund\u2014to help make it happen. That\u2019s where you come in.?? We\u2019re looking for a skilled Editor in Chief to play a critical role in building and overseeing a new project here at Forte that lies at the intersection of video games and blockchain / crypto. In this role, you\u2019ll play an integral part in the project\u2019s impact, helping drive its vision and execution across all applicable areas. If you\u2019re an experienced editor who loves games, writing, technology in equal measures, we want to hear from you!?? In this role, you will\u2026 Help build and oversee all aspects of a new editorial-focused project, including scheduling, writing, editing, resourcing, and publishing.?? Ensure any and all content meets the highest standards of quality and integrity.?? To be a good fit, you have\u2026 15+ years of experience editing and writing, either for media publications or in-house at an organization.?? A natural curiosity and passion for video games, blockchain, and community.?? Impeccable writing, editing, and copy-editing skills.?? The ability to find, extract, and communicate the essence of any story.?? Experience building new audiences in established domains.?? The ability to synthesize seemingly disparate and complex ideas to form a compelling and authentic narrative.?? Exceptional organizational and management skills. First-rate judgement skills in ambiguous situations.?? A collaborate-first mentality but can take an idea and run with it when necessary.?? Appreciation for typography, layout, and visual design. Both print and online editorial experience. Excellent taste when it comes to language and storytelling. Depth of quality industry relationships with a variety of writers, designers, and other creatives. Editorial experience with video, audio, and other multimedia formats. ?? Bonus if you also have\u2026 Experience writing about technical topics and / or broader culture stories. Established social presences. Benefits We believe in treating people right to build a great team for the journey ahead. If there\u2019s something important to you that\u2019s not on this list, talk to us! :) Competitive compensation. Remote and/or flexible work arrangements. We believe in bringing on the best people to our team no matter where they are in the world. A dynamic startup environment where you will constantly be challenged and exposed to new ideas. Whatever equipment helps you get your job done. ", 
